name: 20-Minute Chicken Cutlets & Zucchini Noodles with Creamy Tomato Sauce
ingredients: 1 pound chicken cutlets. ¼ teaspoon salt, divided. ¼ teaspoon ground pepper, divided. 1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil. ½ cup finely chopped red onion. ½ cup dry white wine. ½ cup heavy cream. 1 medium plum tomato, chopped. 2 (10 ounce) packages zucchini noodles
instructions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper. Heat oil in skillet. Cook chicken until browned, 6 min. Transfer. Cook onion. Add wine, reduce. Stir in cream, chicken juices, salt, pepper; simmer. Stir in tomatoes, return chicken. Divide between 4 plates. Cook zucchini noodles. Serve with chicken.

name: Shepherd's Pie with Cauliflower Topping
ingredients: 1 pound lean ground beef. 2 cups chopped onion. 2 tablespoons minced garlic. 1 (15 ounce) can no-salt-added diced tomatoes, drained. 1 tablespoon reduced-sodium Worcestershire sauce. 1 ½ teaspoons chopped fresh rosemary. 3 tablespoons chopped fresh flat-leaf parsley, divided. 1 ½ teaspoons ground pepper, divided. ¾ teaspoon salt, divided. ¼ cup unsalted beef broth. 1 tablespoon all-purpose flour or gluten-free all-purpose flour. 8 cups cauliflower florets (from 1 large head cauliflower). 2 cups water. 6 tablespoons unsalted butter. ¼ cup heavy cream
instructions: Preheat oven to 375°F. Heat skillet. Cook beef, onion, garlic until browned, 8-10 min. Stir in tomatoes, Worcestershire, herbs, seasoning. Whisk broth, flour; stir in. Cook until thickened, 15 min. Boil cauliflower until tender, 10 min. Mash with butter, cream, salt. Spoon over beef. Sprinkle with pepper. Bake until browned, 22-25 min. Sprinkle with parsley before serving.

name: Shrimp Cauliflower Fried Rice
ingredients: ¼ cup sesame oil, divided. 2 large eggs, lightly beaten. 3 cups riced cauliflower (see Tip). 1 pound large shrimp (31-35 count), peeled and deveined. 3 cups broccoli florets. 1 medium red bell pepper, thinly sliced (about 1 cup). 3 cloves garlic, sliced. 3 tablespoons reduced-sodium soy sauce or tamari. 2 tablespoons water. 1 tablespoon rice vinegar. ½ teaspoon ground pepper
instructions: Heat oil in wok. Cook eggs, cut. Cook cauliflower until browned. Cook shrimp until opaque. Cook broccoli, bell pepper, garlic until charred. Stir in soy sauce, water, vinegar, pepper. Add eggs, cauliflower, shrimp.

name: Spicy Noodles with Pork, Scallions & Bok Choy
ingredients: 7 ounces thin rice noodles or rice sticks. 2 tablespoons canola oil, divided. 1 head bok choy (about 1 pound), chopped, greens and whites separated. 3  scallions, sliced, greens and whites separated. 2 tablespoons minced fresh ginger. ¼ cup chili-bean sauce (see Tip) or chile-garlic sauce. 1 pound ground pork. 2 cups unsalted chicken broth. 3 tablespoons reduced-sodium tamari or soy sauce. 1 teaspoon white sugar. 1 tablespoon cornstarch. 1 tablespoon water. Crushed red pepper for garnish
instructions: Cook noodles, drain, rinse. Heat oil in wok. Cook bok choy whites, then greens. Transfer to bowl. Cook scallion whites, ginger, chili-bean sauce in pan. Add pork, cook until no longer pink. Add broth, tamari, sugar. Mix cornstarch, water; add to pan. Bring to boil, cook until thickened. Stir in noodles, bok choy, heat through. Serve topped with scallion greens, crushed red pepper.

name: Chicken Cutlets with Creamy Spinach & Roasted Red Pepper Sauce
ingredients: 1 pound chicken cutlets. ¼ teaspoon salt, divided. ¼ teaspoon ground pepper, divided. 1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil. 1 cup chopped baby spinach. ½ cup finely chopped red onion. ⅓ cup roasted red peppers, thinly sliced. ⅓ cup sun-dried tomato halves, thinly sliced. ½ cup dry white wine. ¾ cup sour cream
instructions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper. Heat oil in skillet. Cook chicken until cooked through, 6 to 8 min. Transfer. Add spinach, onion, roasted red peppers, sun-dried tomatoes to pan. Cook for 1 min. Add wine, reduce. Stir in sour cream, chicken juices, salt, pepper; simmer for 2 min. Return chicken to pan, coat. Serve topped with sauce.

name: Instant-Pot Sausage & Peppers
ingredients: 1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil. 1 (12 ounce) package hot or mild Italian chicken sausage. 1 large white onion, sliced. 1 medium yellow bell pepper, sliced. 1 medium green bell pepper, sliced. 1 large garlic clove, minced. ½ teaspoon dried oregano. ¼ teaspoon crushed red pepper. 1 tablespoon no-salt-added tomato paste. ½ (15 ounce) can no-salt-added crushed tomatoes. 4  Italian sandwich rolls, split and lightly toasted. ¼ cup torn fresh basil
instructions: Select Sauté setting on pressure multicooker, Medium temp, 1-2 min. Add oil, sausage, brown both sides, 4-5 min each. Remove sausage, set aside. Add onion, yellow pepper, green pepper, cook until softened and browned, 5 min. Add garlic, oregano, crushed red pepper, cook until fragrant, 2 min. Add tomato paste, cook for 1 min. Stir in crushed tomatoes, return sausage to cooker, press Cancel. Cover, lock lid, Manual/Pressure Cook setting, High pressure, 5 min. Release steam, venting position, 1-2 min. Remove lid, divide sausage, onions, peppers among rolls. Top with basil, serve immediately.

name: Quinoa-Stuffed Peppers
ingredients: 6 medium red, orange and/or yellow bell peppers. 1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil. 1 large yellow onion, chopped (about 2 cups). 1 tablespoon minced garlic. 1 teaspoon ground cumin. ¾ teaspoon chili powder. 2 teaspoons minced chipotle chiles plus 1 Tbsp. adobo sauce from can. 2 cups cooked tri-color quinoa. 1 (15 ounce) can no-salt-added black beans, rinsed. 1 (14.5 ounce) can no-salt-added diced tomatoes. 1 cup frozen corn. ¼ teaspoon salt. 1 ½ cups shredded pepper Jack cheese
instructions: Preheat oven to 375°F. Cut off bell pepper stems, chop tops (1 cup). Steam peppers until soft, 3 min. Cook onion, chopped pepper tops until soft, 5 min. Stir in garlic, spices, cook, 1 min. Remove from heat, add quinoa, beans, tomatoes, corn, salt; mix. Stand peppers upright in dish, fill with mixture. Cover, bake until warm, 10 min. Sprinkle with cheese, bake until melted, 5-8 min. Rest 5 min before serving.

name: Easy Shrimp Tacos
ingredients: 2 cups diced tomatoes. 1 teaspoon lime zest (reserve before juicing limes). 5 tablespoons lime juice, divided. ¼ cup chopped fresh cilantro. ¼ cup diced red onion. 2 tablespoons minced jalapeño pepper. ⅛ teaspoon salt. 2 tablespoons tahini. ½ teaspoon honey. 1 clove garlic, minced. 2 tablespoons olive oil. 1 tablespoon ground cumin. 2 teaspoons ground coriander. ¼ teaspoon ground pepper. 1 pound large raw shrimp (21-25 count; see Tip), peeled and deveined. 8 (6 inch) flour tortillas, warmed. 1 cup thinly sliced radishes
instructions: Preheat broiler. Combine tomatoes, lime juice, cilantro, onion, jalapeño, salt in bowl; toss. Whisk lime zest, lime juice, tahini, honey, garlic in bowl. Combine oil, cumin, coriander, pepper in large bowl. Add shrimp, coat. Spread on baking sheet. Broil until pink, 4-6 min. To assemble: Place shrimp on tortilla. Top with salsa, tahini sauce, radishes.

name: Egg Roll-Inspired Cabbage Rolls
ingredients: 1 ¼ cups water. 3 tablespoons tomato paste. 2 tablespoons rice vinegar. 2 tablespoons reduced-sodium soy sauce. 4 tablespoons hoisin sauce, divided. 2 tablespoons minced fresh ginger, divided. 4 cloves garlic, minced, divided. ½ teaspoon crushed red pepper. 2 tablespoons cornstarch. 12 large leaves savoy cabbage. 2 cups finely chopped broccoli. 1 pound lean ground pork. 1 ½ cups cooked brown rice. 1  bunch scallions, sliced. 1 teaspoon toasted sesame oil
instructions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Coat baking dish. Whisk water, tomato paste, vinegar, soy sauce, hoisin, ginger, garlic, crushed red pepper in saucepan. Simmer, thicken with cornstarch. Boil cabbage leaves until soft, transfer to baking sheet. Pour hot water over broccoli, refresh with cold water, transfer to bowl. Add pork, rice, scallions, sesame oil, remaining hoisin, ginger, garlic, 3 tbsp reserved sauce. Stir. Fill cabbage leaves with mixture, roll up, place seam-side down in dish. Pour remaining sauce over rolls. Cover with foil, bake until 150°F, about 40 min.

name: Chicken & Zucchini Casserole
ingredients: 3 tablespoons butter, divided. 2 pounds boneless, skinless chicken breast, cut into 1-inch pieces. 2 large zucchini, cut into 1/2-inch pieces. 1 large red bell pepper, chopped. ⅓ cup all-purpose flour. 1 cup no-salt-added chicken broth. 1 cup whole milk. 3 ounces reduced-fat cream cheese. 1 ¼ cups shredded part-skim mozzarella cheese, divided. ¾ teaspoon ground pepper. ½ teaspoon salt
instructions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Melt 1 tbsp butter in skillet. Cook chicken until browned, 8 min. Transfer to bowl. Cook zucchini, bell pepper until soft, 4 min. Transfer to bowl with chicken. Melt remaining 2 tbsp butter in pan. Stir in flour, cook until browned, 1 min. Add broth, milk, bring to boil. Remove from heat, add cream cheese, 3/4 cup mozzarella; stir until melted. Stir in pepper, salt. Drain chicken, vegetables; stir into sauce. Transfer to baking dish, sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Bake until browned, bubbly, 20-25 min. Let stand 10 min before serving.

name: Grilled Flank Steak with Tomato Salad
ingredients: 1 pint grape tomatoes, halved. ½ cup chopped fresh cilantro. ⅓ cup extra-virgin olive oil. 1 small jalapeño pepper, seeded and sliced. 2 teaspoons finely chopped garlic. ½ teaspoon salt, divided. 1 1-pound flank steak. ½ teaspoon ground pepper
instructions: Preheat grill to medium-high. Combine tomatoes, cilantro, oil, jalapeño, garlic, 1/4 tsp salt in bowl. Set aside. Season steak with remaining salt, pepper. Grill until medium-rare, 3-5 min per side. Transfer steak to cutting board, slice thinly across the grain. Divide among plates. Drizzle accumulated juices over steak, top with tomato salad.

name: Cilantro-Lime Chicken Tacos
ingredients: 1 cup loosely packed cilantro leaves, plus 1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro, divided. ¼ cup olive oil. ½ teaspoon lime zest (reserve before juicing limes). 3 tablespoons lime juice, divided. 2 tablespoons orange juice. 2 cloves garlic, minced. ¼ teaspoon salt plus 1/8 tsp., divided. 1 ¼ pounds thin-sliced boneless, skinless chicken cutlets. 1 cup diced tomatoes. 1 cup diced strawberries. 1 tablespoon minced jalapeño pepper. 2 cups baby spinach. 8 (6 inch) blue or yellow corn tortillas, warmed
instructions: Combine cilantro leaves, oil, 2 tbsp lime juice, orange juice, garlic, 1/4 tsp salt in blender; process until smooth. Transfer half to bowl, refrigerate. Place remaining mixture in bag, add chicken. Seal, coat chicken, refrigerate 30 min to 1 hour. Combine tomatoes, strawberries, jalapeño, lime zest, 1 tbsp lime juice, 1/4 cup chopped cilantro, 1/8 tsp salt in bowl; toss. Refrigerate. Preheat grill to medium-high. Remove chicken from marinade, grill until cooked through, 4-5 min per side. Let rest 5 min, slice thinly. To assemble: Place spinach, chicken on tortilla. Top with reserved cilantro mixture, salsa.

name: Coconut Curry Shrimp
ingredients: 2 tablespoons canola oil. 3 tablespoons green curry paste. 1 tablespoon finely chopped garlic. 1 tablespoon finely chopped fresh ginger. 1 ½ teaspoons finely chopped lemongrass. 1 (15 ounce) can light coconut milk, well shaken. 1 cup reduced-sodium vegetable broth. 1 ½ teaspoons fish sauce. 2 teaspoons cornstarch. 6 ounces snow peas, cut into 1-inch pieces. 1 cup matchstick-cut carrots. 2 pounds medium shrimp, peeled and deveined. ½ cup packed fresh Thai basil or Italian basil, thinly sliced. 3 cups hot cooked brown rice
instructions: Heat oil in saucepan over medium heat. Add curry paste, garlic, ginger, lemongrass; cook until aromatic and dry, about 2 min. Add coconut milk, broth; bring to boil. Reduce heat, simmer 5 min. Stir fish sauce, cornstarch in bowl. Add to curry, bring to boil. Reduce heat, simmer until thickened, about 5 min. Add snow peas, carrots; boil until tender, about 2 min. Add shrimp, cook until pink and cooked through, about 2 min. Remove from heat, stir in basil. Serve over rice.

name: Easy Sesame Chicken with Green Beans
ingredients: 4  medium bone-in chicken thighs (about 5 oz. each), skin removed. 4 teaspoons toasted sesame oil or canola oil, divided. ¾ teaspoon garlic powder, divided. ¼ teaspoon salt, divided. 12 ounces green beans, trimmed. 3 tablespoons hoisin sauce. 1 tablespoon sesame seeds, toasted (see Tip). 1 medium scallion, chopped
instructions: Preheat oven to 425°F. Place chicken on baking sheet. Brush with 1 tsp oil, sprinkle with 1/2 tsp garlic powder, 1/8 tsp salt. Roast for 15 min. Toss green beans with remaining 3 tsp oil, 1/4 tsp garlic powder, 1/8 tsp salt. After 15 min, add beans to baking sheet around chicken. Brush chicken with hoisin sauce. Return to oven, roast until chicken registers 165°F, beans are tender and beginning to brown, 10-15 min more. Combine sesame seeds, scallion. Toss half with beans, sprinkle remaining over chicken.

name: Pita Panzanella Salad with Meatballs
ingredients: 1 ½ pounds 93%-lean ground turkey. ½ cup panko breadcrumbs. ¼ cup grated red onion, plus 3/4 cup quartered and thinly sliced. 1  large egg, lightly beaten. 1 tablespoon minced fresh oregano plus 2 tsp., or 1 1/2 tsp. dried oregano, divided. 3 teaspoons minced garlic, divided. 2 teaspoons olive oil plus 3 Tbsp., divided. ¾ teaspoon salt. ½ teaspoon ground pepper. 3 (6 inch) whole-wheat pita breads. 3 tablespoons red-wine vinegar. 1 teaspoon honey. 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard. 1  large English cucumber, sliced. 1 ¾ cups diced plum tomatoes (3-5 tomatoes). ¾ cup sliced pitted Kalamata olives
instructions: Preheat oven to 425°F. Coat baking sheet with cooking spray. Mix turkey, breadcrumbs, grated onion, egg, oregano, garlic, oil, salt, pepper in bowl until combined. Form into about 42 meatballs, 1 inch in diameter. Arrange on baking sheet. Bake until browned, 10-12 min. Split pitas, tear into half-moons. Arrange on baking sheet, bake until golden brown, 5-7 min. Let cool, break into croutons. Whisk vinegar, remaining oil, oregano, garlic, honey, mustard in bowl. Add cucumber, tomatoes, olives, onion, pita croutons; toss. Serve salad with meatballs.

name: Baked Fish & Kale Lavash Wraps
ingredients: 5 ounces baby kale or baby spinach. 3 tablespoons coarsely chopped fresh tarragon and/or dill. 2 tablespoons finely chopped scallions. ½ teaspoon kosher salt, divided. ⅛ teaspoon plus 1/4 teaspoon ground pepper, divided. 1 pound cod, halibut or barramundi, skinned and cut into 4 portions. 4 sheets lavash. 6 teaspoons extra-virgin olive oil, divided. ¼ cup Very Versatile Roasted Red Pepper Sauce (see Associated Recipes), plus more for serving
instructions: Preheat oven to 375°F. Line baking sheet with parchment paper, coat with spray. Wilt greens in boiling water for 5 min, drain. Mix with tarragon, scallions, salt, pepper. Season fish. Place fish on lavash, top with greens, roll up. Bake 20-30 min until crisp. Serve with sauce.

name: Pork & Pineapple Tacos
ingredients: 1 tablespoon chili powder. 2 teaspoons smoked paprika. 1 teaspoon packed light brown sugar. ¾ teaspoon salt, divided. ½ teaspoon garlic powder. ½ teaspoon ground pepper. 1 (2 pound) pork loin roast, trimmed. ⅓ cup apple juice. ½ cup lime juice. 2 cups finely diced fresh pineapple (about 1/2 small pineapple). 1 cup finely diced seeded cucumber. ¼ cup finely diced red onion. 2 tablespoons cider vinegar. 12  6-inch corn tortillas, warmed. 2 cups shredded red cabbage
instructions: Combine chili powder, paprika, brown sugar, 1/2 tsp salt, garlic powder, pepper. Rub spice mixture over pork in slow cooker. Pour apple juice around pork. Cook on Low 6-7 hours until fork-tender. Combine lime juice, 1/4 tsp salt in bowl. Add pineapple, cucumber, onion; toss. Refrigerate. Skim fat from juices in slow cooker. Shred meat, stir in vinegar. To assemble tacos: Place pulled pork on tortilla, add cooking liquid, shredded cabbage, pineapple salsa.

name: Coconut-Curry Chicken Cutlets
ingredients: 2 tablespoons grapeseed oil, divided. 1 pound chicken cutlets. 1 (14 ounce) can light coconut milk. 1 tablespoon brown sugar. 1 tablespoon red Thai curry paste (see Tip). 1 tablespoon lime juice. 2 cups cooked quinoa. Chopped fresh cilantro for garnish
instructions: Heat 1 tbsp oil in skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken, cook until browned and cooked through, 1-3 min per side. Transfer to plate. Remove pan from heat. Whisk remaining 1 tbsp oil, coconut milk, brown sugar, curry paste, lime juice in pan. Cook over high heat until reduced by half, 5-10 min. Serve chicken with quinoa and sauce, garnished with cilantro if desired.

name: Pho-Inspired Beef Noodle Soup
ingredients: 1 teaspoon canola oil. 3 cloves garlic, minced. 1 tablespoon minced fresh ginger. 1 teaspoon ground pepper. ¼ teaspoon ground cinnamon. ¼ teaspoon ground cloves. 4 cups unsalted beef broth. 1 tablespoon fish sauce. 4 ounces pad thai rice noodles. 2 cups halved snap peas. 1 cup thinly sliced white onion. 1 pound beef sirloin, thinly sliced. 1 cup bean sprouts. ½ cup thinly sliced scallions (4 medium). ¼ cup thinly sliced fresh basil. ¼ cup thinly sliced chile peppers, such as serrano or jalapeño. Lime wedges for serving
instructions: Heat oil in pot over medium heat. Add garlic, ginger, pepper, cinnamon, cloves; cook 1 min. Stir in broth, fish sauce; bring to boil. Reduce heat, simmer partially covered 15 min. Meanwhile, cook noodles according to package. Drain, divide among 4 bowls. Add snap peas, onion, beef to broth. Simmer until beef is just cooked through, about 1 min; remove from heat. Ladle soup over noodles. Divide bean sprouts, scallions, basil, chiles among bowls. Serve with lime wedges.

name: Spice-Seared Salmon with Greek-Style Green Beans
ingredients: 2 tablespoons olive oil, divided. 1 small yellow onion, diced. 4 cloves garlic, chopped. 1 (15 ounce) can no-salt-added diced tomatoes. 2 tablespoons chopped fresh dill, divided. ½ teaspoon salt, divided. 12 ounces green beans, stem ends trimmed (4 cups). ¼ cup lemon juice. 1 pound salmon fillet with skin, cut into 4 portions. 1 tablespoon Baharat Spice Mix (see Associated Recipes)
instructions: Preheat oven to 425°F. Line baking sheet with parchment paper, coat with spray. Heat 1 tbsp oil in saucepan over medium heat. Add onion, cook until translucent, 3-5 min. Stir in garlic, cook 1 min. Stir in tomatoes, 1 tbsp dill, 1/4 tsp salt; bring to boil. Stir in green beans. Reduce heat, cover, simmer until tender, 10-15 min. Meanwhile, whisk lemon juice, 1 tbsp oil in shallow bowl. Dip salmon in lemon-oil mixture. Place salmon, skin-side down, on baking sheet. Sprinkle with spice mix, remaining 1/4 tsp salt. Roast salmon until opaque in center, about 10 min. Divide green bean mixture among 4 plates, add salmon, sprinkle with remaining 1 tbsp dill.

name: Mushroom-Swiss Turkey Burgers
ingredients: 2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil. 1 clove garlic, minced. ¾ teaspoon ground pepper, divided. ½ teaspoon salt, divided. 8  portobello mushroom caps, stems and gills removed (see Tips). 1 pound lean ground turkey. 2 teaspoons gluten-free Worcestershire sauce. 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard. 4 slices Swiss cheese. 1 small tomato, thinly sliced. 3 cups baby arugula
instructions: Preheat grill to medium-high. Brush portobello caps with oil mixture; let marinate. Shape turkey mixture into patties. Grill mushrooms until tender, about 4 minutes per side. Transfer to plate; cover. Grill turkey patties until cooked through, about 4-5 minutes per side. Add cheese during last minute. Let patties rest. Place each patty on a portobello cap; top with tomato slices and arugula. Cover with remaining caps. Serve.

name: Air-Fryer Meatloaf
ingredients: 1 pound 90%-lean ground beef. ½ pound ground pork. 1  large egg, lightly beaten. ½ cup Italian-seasoned panko breadcrumbs. ¼ cup finely chopped yellow onion. ¼ cup chopped fresh parsley. 1 ½ tablespoons Worcestershire sauce. 2 cloves garlic, minced. ½ teaspoon kosher salt. ½ teaspoon ground pepper. 5 tablespoons ketchup, divided
instructions: Preheat air fryer to 350°F. Mix beef, pork, egg, panko, onion, parsley, Worcestershire, garlic, salt, pepper, 3 tbsp ketchup. Form into loaves. Cook in air fryer until 155°F, about 25 min. Brush with 2 tbsp ketchup. Continue cooking until 165°F, about 3 min. Rest 5 min before slicing.

name: Instant Pot Beef Bourguignon
ingredients: 1 ¾ pounds beef stew meat, preferably chuck, trimmed and cut into 1 1/4-inch chunks. ¾ teaspoon salt, divided. ½ teaspoon ground pepper. 8 teaspoons canola oil, divided. ⅔ cup dry red wine. 1 large onion, chopped (1 1/2 cups). 1 cup diced carrots (2 medium). 4 cloves garlic, minced. ¾ teaspoon dried thyme leaves. 1 (15 ounce) can no-salt-added diced tomatoes. 1 cup low-sodium beef broth. 1  bay leaf. 1 pound cremini or button mushrooms, quartered (5 cups). 2 cups frozen pearl onions (8 oz.). 2 tablespoons cornstarch. 2 tablespoons water. 1-2 teaspoons red-wine or cider vinegar. 2 tablespoons chopped fresh parsley for garnish
instructions: Pat beef dry; sprinkle with salt, pepper. Brown beef in skillet, transfer to plate. Add wine to skillet, cook until reduced. Meanwhile, sauté onion, carrots, garlic, thyme in multicooker. Add tomatoes, broth, beef, wine reduction. Pressure cook for 40 min. Sauté mushrooms separately. Cook pearl onions. Release pressure, stir in cornstarch mixture. Add mushrooms, pearl onions. Garnish with parsley.

name: Coconut-Curry Cod Stew with Sweet Potato & Rice
ingredients: 2 cups water. ¾ cup long-grain brown rice. 1 tablespoon canola oil. 1 tablespoon chopped fresh ginger. 1 tablespoon chopped garlic. 1  yellow bell pepper, halved, seeded, and sliced. 1 pound sweet potatoes (about 2 small or 1 large), peeled and cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces. 1 tablespoon curry powder. ½ teaspoon salt. 1 (15 ounce) can light coconut milk. 4  cod fillets (4-5 oz. each). 3 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro, plus more for garnish. 2 teaspoons lime juice
instructions: Cook rice according to package instructions. In a skillet, sauté ginger and garlic. Add bell pepper, sweet potatoes, curry powder, salt, and coconut milk. Simmer until sweet potatoes are tender, about 10-15 minutes. Nestle cod fillets into the pan; cover and cook until soft, 5-8 minutes. Stir in cilantro and lime juice. Serve over rice. Garnish with cilantro if desired.

name: Stuffed Sweet Potatoes with Chili
ingredients: 2 small sweet potatoes (about 8 oz. each). 1 tablespoon canola oil. 8 ounces 95%-lean ground beef. 2  scallions, sliced, green and white parts separated. 2 tablespoons tomato paste. 1-2 canned chipotle peppers in adobo, chopped. 1 tablespoon paprika. ¼ teaspoon salt. 1 cup canned low-sodium kidney beans, rinsed. ½ cup water. ¼ cup shredded Mexican-blend cheese. 4 teaspoons reduced-fat sour cream for garnish
instructions: Preheat oven to 425°F. Bake sweet potatoes until tender, about 40-45 minutes. In a skillet, cook beef, scallion whites, and seasonings. Mix in beans until liquid evaporates. Scoop sweet potato flesh into a bowl, mix with chili, and fill potato skins. Top with chili and cheese. Bake until cheese melts, 3-5 minutes. Garnish with scallion greens.

name: Greek-Inspired Burgers with Herb-Feta Sauce
ingredients: 1 cup nonfat plain Greek yogurt. ¼ cup crumbled feta cheese. 3 tablespoons chopped fresh oregano, divided. ¼ teaspoon lemon zest. 2 teaspoons lemon juice. ¾ teaspoon salt, divided. 1 small red onion. 1 pound ground lamb or ground beef. ½ teaspoon ground pepper. 2  whole-wheat pitas, halved, split and warmed. 1 cup sliced cucumber. 1  plum tomato, sliced
instructions: Preheat grill or broiler. Mix yogurt, feta, lemon zest, lemon juice, and oregano. Combine chopped onion, meat, oregano, salt, and pepper. Shape into patties. Grill or broil until cooked through. Serve in pita halves with sauce, onion slices, cucumber, and tomato.

name: Sheet-Pan Chicken Fajita Bowls
ingredients: 2 teaspoons chili powder. 2 teaspoons ground cumin. ¾ teaspoon salt, divided. ½ teaspoon garlic powder. ½ teaspoon smoked paprika. ¼ teaspoon ground pepper. 2 tablespoons olive oil, divided. 1 ¼ pounds chicken tenders. 1 medium yellow onion, sliced. 1 medium red bell pepper, sliced. 1 medium green bell pepper, sliced. 4 cups chopped stemmed kale. 1 (15 ounce) can no-salt-added black beans, rinsed. ¼ cup low-fat plain Greek yogurt. 1 tablespoon lime juice. 2 teaspoons water
instructions: Preheat oven to 425°F with a baking sheet inside. Combine spices, then mix with chicken, onion, and bell peppers. Coat the pan with cooking spray and spread chicken mixture. Roast for 15 minutes. Toss kale and beans with oil and salt. Remove pan, stir chicken and veggies, then add kale and beans. Roast until chicken is cooked and veggies tender. Mix yogurt, lime juice, and water. Serve chicken and veggies with yogurt dressing.

name: Turkey & Sweet Potato Chili
ingredients: 1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil. 1 pound ground turkey. 1 large yellow onion, chopped. 3 cloves garlic, minced. 1 tablespoon minced seeded canned chipotle pepper in adobo sauce. 1 (28 ounce) can no-salt-added diced tomatoes. 2 medium sweet potatoes (about 5 oz. each), peeled and diced. 2 cups unsalted chicken broth. ¾ teaspoon salt. 2 tablespoons lime juice. Chopped avocado for garnish
instructions: Heat oil in a large pot. Add turkey, onion, and garlic; cook until turkey is browned and onion is softened. Stir in chipotle, tomatoes, sweet potatoes, broth, and salt. Simmer until sweet potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes. Uncover and simmer until slightly thickened, about 10 minutes more. Stir in lime juice. Serve chili in bowls, garnished with avocado if desired.

name: Chicken Parmesan Pizza
ingredients: 1 pound whole-wheat pizza dough. 1 ½ cups shredded cooked chicken breast (8 ounces). ¾ cup pizza sauce, divided. ¼ teaspoon garlic powder. ¼ teaspoon crushed red pepper. All-purpose flour for rolling dough. 1 cup shredded low-fat mozzarella cheese or 4 ounces fresh mozzarella, torn into pieces. ½ cup grated Parmesan cheese, divided. ¼ cup thinly sliced fresh basil
instructions: Preheat oven to 475°F and coat a baking sheet with cooking spray. Mix chicken, 1/4 cup pizza sauce, garlic powder, and crushed red pepper. Roll out pizza dough and transfer to baking sheet. Spread remaining pizza sauce over dough, then top with chicken mixture, mozzarella, and 1/4 cup Parmesan. Bake for 16-20 minutes. Sprinkle with basil and remaining Parmesan before cutting into 10 pieces.

name: Parchment Packet Baked Tuna Steaks & Vegetables with Creamy Dijon-Turmeric Sauce
ingredients: ¼ cup mayonnaise. 1 tablespoon chopped fresh parsley. 2 teaspoons Dijon mustard. 1 teaspoon honey. ½ teaspoon ground turmeric. 2 cups thinly sliced Yukon Gold potatoes (about 1/8-inch). ½ teaspoon salt, divided. ⅛ teaspoon ground pepper, plus 1/4 teaspoon, divided. 4 cups chopped kale. 1 ¼ pounds tuna (about 1 inch thick), cut into 4 pieces
instructions: Preheat oven to 450°F. Mix mayonnaise, parsley, mustard, honey, and turmeric. Fold parchment sheets in half, then open. Place potatoes, kale, and tuna on one side of each sheet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then brush with the mayonnaise mixture. Close and seal packets, then bake for 10-15 minutes. Let stand for 3 minutes, then carefully open and serve.

name: Green Chicken Curry
ingredients: 2 tablespoons canola oil. 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken thighs, trimmed, cut into bite-size pieces. 1 bunch scallions, sliced. 1  medium sweet potato, cut into 1/2-inch cubes. 1 14-ounce can “lite” coconut milk. 2 tablespoons Thai green, red or yellow curry paste. 1 tablespoon fish sauce. 3 cups sliced bok choy. 1 ½ cups halved green beans, fresh or frozen (thawed). ¼ cup chopped fresh basil. 1 tablespoon lime juice
instructions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook chicken and scallions until chicken is no longer pink, about 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a plate. Add sweet potato to the skillet; cook for 2 minutes. Stir in coconut milk, curry paste, fish sauce, bok choy, and green beans; simmer covered until vegetables are tender, 5-7 minutes. Return chicken to the skillet; cook until heated through, about 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in basil and lime juice.

name: Slow-Cooker Braised Beef with Carrots & Turnips
ingredients: 1 tablespoon kosher salt. 2 teaspoons ground cinnamon. ½ teaspoon ground allspice. ½ teaspoon ground pepper. ¼ teaspoon ground cloves. 3-3 1/2 pounds beef chuck roast, trimmed. 2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil. 1 medium onion, chopped. 3 cloves garlic, sliced. 1 cup red wine. 1 (28 ounce) can whole tomatoes, preferably San Marzano. 5 medium carrots, cut into 1-inch pieces. 2 medium turnips, peeled and cut into 1/2-inch pieces. Chopped fresh basil for garnish
instructions: Rub beef with spice mixture. Brown in skillet. Transfer to slow cooker with onion, garlic, wine, tomatoes, carrots, and turnips. Cook on High 4 hours or Low 8 hours. Serve sliced beef with vegetables and sauce. Garnish with basil if desired.

name: Oven-Baked Salmon with Charred Onions & Old Bay Radishes
ingredients: 2 medium onions, sliced 1/2 inch thick. 4 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil, divided. Zest of 2 lemons. 1 ½ teaspoons cracked pepper. 1 teaspoon kosher salt, divided. 4 (5 ounce) skin-on salmon fillets. 6 large radishes, cut into wedges, plus more thinly sliced for garnish. 1 teaspoon Old Bay seasoning. ½ teaspoon sugar. Fresh cilantro & flaky sea salt for garnish
instructions: Preheat oven to 325°F. Char onions in a cast-iron skillet. Transfer to a bowl and let steam. Mix oil, lemon zest, pepper, and salt. Spread mixture on salmon. Bake for 14-16 minutes. Boil radish wedges until tender. Heat oil and Old Bay in a skillet. Add radishes. Puree onions with salt and sugar. Serve salmon with onion puree and radishes. Garnish with sliced radishes, cilantro, and flaky salt if desired.

name: Spicy Slow-Cooker Chicken with Lime, Basil & Mint
ingredients: 3 cups low-sodium chicken broth. 3  shallots, very thinly sliced. ¼ cup fish sauce (see Tips). 2 tablespoons packed light brown sugar. 2-4 Thai chiles, very thinly sliced, or 1 teaspoon crushed red pepper. 2 teaspoons lime zest. 4 pounds skin-on, bone-in chicken breasts. 2 cups julienned or grated carrots. ½ cup lime juice. ⅓ cup sliced fresh mint. ⅓ cup sliced fresh basil
instructions: Combine broth, shallots, fish sauce, brown sugar, chiles (or crushed red pepper), and lime zest in a slow cooker. Add chicken, cook on High for 3 hours or Low for 6 hours. Remove chicken, shred meat, discard skin. Return chicken to slow cooker, add carrots, lime juice, mint, and basil. Stir and serve.

name: Ginger-Orange Chicken Thighs with Baby Bok Choy
ingredients: 2 pounds bone-in chicken thighs. ½ teaspoon Chinese five-spice powder. ¼ teaspoon salt. 2 teaspoons peanut oil. 1 ½ pounds baby bok choy, halved. 1 (11 ounce) can mandarin oranges in light syrup, drained. 2 tablespoons reduced-sodium tamari. 2 tablespoons Shaoxing rice wine or dry sherry, divided. 2 tablespoons minced shallot. 1 tablespoon grated garlic. 1 tablespoon grated fresh ginger. 1 ½ teaspoons cornstarch
instructions: Preheat oven to 450°F. Pat chicken dry, season with five-spice powder and salt. Heat oil in a skillet, brown chicken skin-side down for 6-8 minutes. Flip chicken, add bok choy, then transfer to oven. Roast until chicken reaches 165°F, about 15 minutes. In a saucepan, simmer 1/4 cup mandarin orange syrup, tamari, rice wine, shallot, garlic, and ginger for 3 minutes. Whisk remaining rice wine and cornstarch, add to sauce. Cook until thickened, about 1 minute. Strain sauce, stir in reserved oranges. Serve chicken and bok choy with sauce.

name: Creamy Skillet Ranch Chicken & Broccoli
ingredients: 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breast, trimmed and cut into bite-size pieces. ½ teaspoon salt, divided. ½ teaspoon ground pepper, divided, plus more for garnish. 2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil, divided. 4 cups bite-size broccoli florets. 2 tablespoons water. ½ cup heavy cream. 2 tablespoons white-wine vinegar. 2 tablespoons mayonnaise. 1 teaspoon cornstarch. ½ teaspoon onion powder. ½ teaspoon garlic powder. ¼ cup chopped mixed fresh herbs (chives, dill, tarragon, basil)
instructions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Cook in oil until browned and cooked through. Transfer to plate. Cook broccoli until tender-crisp; transfer to plate. Whisk cream mixture, add to pan, simmer until thickened. Return chicken and broccoli to pan, cook until heated through. Garnish with herbs.

name: Creamy Chicken, Brussels Sprouts & Mushrooms One-Pot Pasta
ingredients: 8 ounces whole-wheat linguine or spaghetti. 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken thighs. 4 cups sliced mushrooms. 2 cups sliced Brussels sprouts. 1 medium onion, chopped. 4 cloves garlic, thinly sliced. 2 tablespoons Boursin cheese. 1 ¼ teaspoons dried thyme. ¾ teaspoon dried rosemary. ¾ teaspoon salt. 4 cups water. 2 tablespoons chopped fresh chives
instructions: Combine all ingredients except chives in a large pot. Bring to a boil, then simmer until pasta is cooked and water has reduced, about 10-12 minutes. Let stand for 5 minutes, then serve sprinkled with chives.
